ue with the cream lace hat and she put a cornflower blue flower on the side - side back - something blue. But it was very kind of her. And Edith, her sister, was my bridesmaid - that's how I come to call Edith after her. See? And we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15802361 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5862339\charrsid6432729  and my husband was in khaki. He had - the breeches. Not the putties - not putties - breeches - special.
